10/06/2022

Java Operators:

1. Arithmetic Operators (+, -, *, etc.)
2. Assignment Operators (=, +=, -+)
    - String name; -> declaration
    - name = "Monica" -> assigning the value
    - System.out.println(name); -> Monica
    - name = "Robert"; -> change value or re-assigning
    - System.out.println(name); -> Robert

   String name = "Monica"; -> initialized variable

3. Comparison Operators (==, >, <, >=, <=)
4. Logical Operators( ||, |, &, &&) -> true/false
5. Bitwise Operators(high level)

IF STATEMENT:

regular if:
int age = 20;
if (age == 1500){
System.out.println("TRUE");
} else {
System.out.println("FALSE");
}

else -> default, gets executed, when if condition is not met
else if -> is a keyword where we execute one more extra condition

ladder if:


nested if:
int age = 20;
char gender = 'F';

if (age ==20){
    if (char == 'M') {
    System.out.println("Wrong age!");
    } else if (char == 'F'){
    System.out.println("You are correct!");
    } else {
    System.out.println("Program supports only F or M");
    }
} else {
    System.out.println("Sorry, our program only supports the users of 20 y.o.");
}